name: Rules of Engagement
overview: Rules of Engagement is a comedy about the different phases of male/female relationships, as seen through the eyes of a newly engaged couple, Adam and Jennifer, a long-time married pair, Jeff and Audrey, and a single guy on the prowl, Russell. As they find out, the often confusing stages of a relationship can seem like being on a roller coaster. People can describe the ride to you, but to really know what it's like you have to experience it for yourself.

seasons.name: Season 6
seasons.overview:
The sixth season of the American television comedy series Rules of Engagement initially received a 24-episode order and was set to debut on Saturday, October 15, 2011, but relocated to Thursdays due to the low ratings developing from How to Be a Gentleman. After CBS announced the two comedies would swap timeslots, they set the Season 6 debut as October 20, 2011 at 8:30 PM.

Effective January 12, 2012, CBS removed Rules of Engagement from its Thursday lineup, replacing it with the new sitcom Rob starring Rob Schneider. CBS announced that Rules would return to its Thursday 8:30 PM time slot at a later date. After Rob's run of its initial eight episode order, Rules returned March 29 for eight weeks of new episodes. Thus, the sixth season was cut from 24 episodes to 15.

seasons.name: Season 7
seasons.overview: The seventh and final season of the American television comedy series Rules of Engagement received a 13-episode order on May 21, 2012, and premiered on Monday, February 4, 2013. On May 10, 2013, CBS cancelled Rules of Engagement, stating that the May 20, 2013 season finale would also be the series finale.

episodes.name: Pilot
episodes.overview: Married couple Jeff and Audrey have just learned their next door neighbor, Jennifer, has become engaged to her boyfriend, Adam. But when Jeff tries to give Adam advice, he develops doubt about the impending engagement. Meanwhile, Jennifer fixes up Adam's best friend, Russell, because she believes the right woman could change his habit of being a serial dater. Meanwhile, Jeff inadvertently starts a fight between Audrey and himself about an old bicycle.

episodes.name: The Birthday Deal
episodes.overview: When it's time to plan a party for Jeff's birthday, everyone gets involved. But Audrey is spending a little too much time on planning the party, which makes Jeff unhappy. Alhough Jeff won't reveal what he usually gets in the annual birthday deal, Adam brings up the subject with Jennifer and is then worried when Jennifer not only agrees to give him a birthday deal, but announces she wants to get one in return. Meanwhile, Russell is obsessed with trying to figure out what Jeff's birthday present really is.

episodes.name: Young and the Restless
episodes.overview: While Russell has a hot new date, Audrey bets Jeff that he can't score a phone number from a younger woman and gives him a night without his wedding ring to try.

episodes.name: Game On
episodes.overview: Jeff puts Audrey in a bad mood after he fails to respond to the news of her big promotion at work because he is watching his basketball game. Jeff tries to make it up by inviting her to floor seats at a Knicks game. But she can't decide what to wear, which it makes Jeff wonder if she cares more about how she looks than about him. Now that Jennifer and Adam are living together, they have an argument over money.

episodes.name: Kids
episodes.overview: Russell accidentally bumps into an older woman from his past, Constance. He then decides to show her his physical prowess.

episodes.name: Hard Day's Night
episodes.overview: Jeff is in trouble. He doesn't know how to tell Audrey that he got "excited" while Jennifer was giving him a massage to thank him for helping her move a couch. Now, Jeff must face Audrey.

episodes.name: Jeff's Wooby
episodes.overview: Audrey is scared by Jeff's constant reminiscing about each t-shirt's significance. After a little while, she starts to wonder if his  best times in life may have come before her.

1.name: Season 1

episodes.overview: Jeff's snoring has gotten out of hands. Audrey, who isn't able to sleep anymore, decides that she and Jeff should sleep in separate bedrooms. While this could seems like a bad situation for some, other like Jeff see the good side of it. Jeff takes advantage of his new found freedom by staying up too late and living like a college student.

episodes.overview: With Audrey's sister, Barbara, having problems in her marriage, the only thing she doesn't need is a man who would trick her to try and get her to sleep with him. But, sadly, in Audrey's life there is a man just like this. During this episode, Russel will try everything to get a one night stand with Audrey's sister.

episodes.name: Mr. Fix It
episodes.overview: Jeff finds himself in trouble when he tries to fix an issue Audrey is having with one of their neighbors.

episodes.name: Guy Code
episodes.overview: Audrey gets a lesson about the 'guy code' when Jeff shares a secret about a new friend.

episodes.name: Bag Ladies
episodes.overview: Jeff suddenly feels he has nothing to talk about with the guys so he feels the only way to connect with the guys is to talk about sex. Jeff and Audrey need to come up with a different topic and leave the discussion of sex for the bedroom.

episodes.name: Old School Jeff
episodes.overview: Jeff has a rare opportunity to have a night with the guys rather than go to a wedding.  Will Audreyâ€™s fear about Jeff come true?

episodes.name: Engagement Party
episodes.overview: Barbara returns to town with news that could have Russell very happy.

episodes.name: Fix-up & Downs
episodes.overview: Audrey and Jennifer decide to do some match making and will be surprised at who is helped by it.

episodes.name: A Visit from Fay
episodes.overview: Can Jennifer survive the visit from Fay and how will Jeff Audrey deal with no TV?

episodes.name: Time Share
episodes.overview: Jennifer and Adam decide to go on a trip with Jeff and Audrey but may have wished they had stayed home when they find out the reason they took the trip.

episodes.name: Jen at Work
episodes.overview: Adam wants Russell to agree to hire Jen to design an ad campaign for one of their clients. He will not listen to Russell and Jeff when they tell him that this is not a good idea. When Audrey shares the fertility issues with Jen, she gives them a gift to help bring them luck.

episodes.name: Optimal Male
episodes.overview: Jeff becomes obsessed to lose a few pounds so he can qualify for a better rate on his life insurance. Adam happens to see an ex-girlfriend, Jennifer becomes very jealous.

episodes.name: Russell's Father's Son
episodes.overview: When Adam ends up being asked to appear in a promotional video being shot by Russell's father, he worries about hurting Russell's feelings.

episodes.name: Buyer's Remorse
episodes.overview: Adam and Jennifer are looking to move and find an apartment in the same Building as Audrey and Jeff. Jeff and Audrey agree to support them to the board, only Jeff has a run in with a board member.

episodes.name: Pimp My Bride
episodes.overview: Russell tries another approach to get the girl. Will using his apartment for a photo shoot seal the deal?  Also Adam and Jennifer have a wedding date picked.

No new episodes of the program aired between December and March, due to the 2007-2008 Writers Guild of America strike.

episodes.name: Russell's Secret
episodes.overview: Audrey discovers that Russell is really a closet Broadway-musical fan, and uses this knowledge to her advantage by blackmailing him for tickets. Meanwhile, Adam and Jennifer decide to take dancing lessons.

episodes.name: Voluntary Commitment
episodes.overview: Audrey has to keep her bet to Jeff by finishing what she starts. We meet Russell's new assistant.

episodes.name: Jeff's New Friend
episodes.overview: Jeff learns a fact about a friend he just met at the gym and Russell has doubts about the family history of a new girlfriend.

episodes.name: Dad's Visit
episodes.overview: Jeff's father arrives after spraining his ankle and expects Audrey to wait on him hand and foot while he recooperates. Meanwhile, Russell begins to regret a one-night stand after she won't leave his apartment.

episodes.overview: Jeff and Audrey are invited to dinner with Jennifer and Adam, but tell a lie so they can attend a better bash that evening. Russell also attends the same party and manages to offend former NFL great, Jerry Rice.

episodes.name: Poaching Timmy
episodes.overview: When Timmy gets tired of Russell's demands and Audrey gets fed up with her terrible assistant, the two work together to find a solution. Meanwhile, Jeff's supersition gets the best of him as he tries to recreate the exact conditions of the Giants' win.

episodes.name: Old Timer's Day
episodes.overview: After being harrassed for falling asleep during a movie, Jeff tries to prove to Audrey that he's still young by inviting her to his softball game.

episodes.name: Twice
episodes.overview: Frustrated over the attention a pregnant co-worker is getting, Audrey pretends she too is pregnant in order to get special treatment.

episodes.name: The Challenge
episodes.overview: Russell issues a competition between the guys to see who can convince their partners to engage in sex more easily.

episodes.name: Family Style
episodes.overview: Jeff doesn't get any dinner after someone else eats it before Jeff does now he has to keep quiet about it.

episodes.name: May Divorce Be with You
episodes.overview: Audrey makes a bad mistake after a friend, whose marriage is falling a part is doing something bad when he hugs people.

episodes.name: House Money
episodes.overview: Audrey convinces Jeff to go out on the town and do something exciting after making a profit from the sale of his car. After the lavish night has finished, she regrets the decision after finding out they spent much more than he made.

episodes.name: Sex Toy Story
episodes.overview: After Jennifer hosts a party, Jeff wonders if he and Audrey are missing out on something in their personal life.

It consists of 13 episodes, each running approximately 22 minutes in length. CBS broadcast the third season at 9:30 pm in the United States.

episodes.name: Flirting
episodes.overview: Jeff listens to Russell about a co-worker and finds himself in trouble. Timmy is sent to get Russell's phone from the apartment of his most recent conquest.

episodes.name: Snoozin' for a Bruisin'
episodes.overview: When Jeff and Audrey switch sides of the bed, Jeff accidentally rolls over and clocks Audrey in the face, landing her in the hospital.

episodes.name: Atlantic City
episodes.overview: Audrey tries to make Jeff feel guilty for not telling her that his friend's bachelor party in Atlantic City was cancelled; however, her plan backfires when Jeff discovers that Audrey is also being deceitful.

episodes.overview: Audrey is upset when Jeff reveals to her that he doesn't believe she saw her dead grandmother's ghost. Meanwhile, Russell tries to persuade Timmy not to go through with his arranged marriage.

episodes.name: The Four Pillars
episodes.overview: To make Audrey happy, Jeff begrudgingly agrees to see a couple's therapist. Meanwhile, Russell develops a crush on Timmy's fiance.

episodes.name: 3rd Wheel
episodes.overview: Unbeknownst to Jeff, Audrey lies to her homely friend Liz that she is on Jeff's list of woman he would sleep with if Audrey wasn't around.

episodes.name: Indian Giver
episodes.overview: Audrey is surprised by Jeff's sudden interest in her favorite reality show until she discovers the reason. Meanwhile, to Russell's delight, Timmy has second thoughts about his impending arranged marriage.

episodes.name: Free Free Time
episodes.overview: Jeff and Audrey have trouble spending time apart after their plans don't work out. Russell finds out that Timmy is harboring some ill feelings toward him.

episodes.name: The Score
episodes.overview:
Jeff really can't stand not knowing the score of the NY Rangers game and has to try hard to get the game off his mind while at a party for Audrey's boss.

Russell is mad at Timmy because he doesn't root for the home team.

episodes.name: The Surrogate
episodes.overview: Audrey is over bearing with a potential surrogate mother for her and Jeff. Russell finds Jennifer and Adam's wedding web site and teases them about it.

episodes.name: Reunion
episodes.overview: Audrey attends her high school reunion intent on proving to her former classmates how great her life is in New York City. Meanwhile, Russell accidentally ruins Timmy's dinner party.

episodes.name: Harassment
episodes.overview: A new employee with an axe to grind against Audrey files a sexual harassment claim against her. Meanwhile, after being teased for playing cricket, Timmy challenges Jeff to a game to prove the sport is not for wimps.

episodes.name: They Do?
episodes.overview: Adam and Jennifer plan a secret wedding; however, a series of unfortunate events puts their plan in jeopardy. Meanwhile, to keep Russell and Timmy from finding out about the ceremony, Adam tells them he is staging an intervention for Jeff, on the fourth season finale of RULES OF ENGAGEMEN.

CBS broadcast the fourth season on Monday at 8:30 pm in the United States between How I Met Your Mother and Two and a Half Men.

episodes.name: Surro-gate
episodes.overview: Jeff unsuccessfully tries to keep Russell from sleeping with their new surrogate, while Adam tries to work on improving his rear end.

episodes.overview: Jeff tells Adam his secret for keeping track of Audrey's mistakes and how he uses that list to keep Audrey from getting too upset with him when he makes mistakes. Russell hoping to get a girl sends a nasty e-mail to Timmy's love interest.

episodes.name: Rug-Of-War
episodes.overview: Jeff wants to see if he can get Audrey to get the rug back after Jeff gets sentimental about the rug and reminds Audrey about all the good times they had on that rug.

episodes.name: Handy Man
episodes.overview: Audrey tries to be more spontaneous in the bedroom with Jeff. Meanwhile, Russell invites Timmy to join him on a business trip to distract him from his fear of flying.

episodes.name: Play Ball

episodes.name: Baked

episodes.overview: When Jeff can't get out of the lease for a retail space he rented for Audrey's fleeting cookie business, he and Adam invent a new game involving the heads of mannequins. Meanwhile, Russell and Timmy go on a double date.

episodes.name: Les-bro

episodes.name: The Big Picture
episodes.overview: When Russell's trust fund is cut off by his mother, he gets a taste of how life will be after moving in with Timmy. Meanwhile, Audrey helps Jeff impress his boss in order to get a raise.

episodes.name: Fun Run
episodes.overview: Jeff struggles to figure out how to ask his co-workers to donate money for Audrey's 10K charity run after telling them that he doesn't want to participate in their fundraisers anymore.

episodes.name: Refusing to Budget
episodes.overview: Timmy teaches Russell how to budget after all utilities are suddenly turned off. Audrey tells someone all about publishing and shows off her office.

episodes.name: Little Bummer Boy
episodes.overview: When Russell decides to borrow a Holiday concept of gift-giving from Adam, both Adam and his co-workers are in for surprises. Meanwhile, Audrey wants to make people laugh at Jeff's Holiday party.

episodes.name: The Home Stretch
episodes.overview: When Jeff discovers that a guy is giving Audrey home pilates classes, he wants to make a change. Meanwhile, Adam tells Jennifer specifics about his football past.

episodes.name: Uh Oh It's Magic
episodes.overview: Russell is busy looking for his date at a magic show, Audrey tells Brenda's girlfriend a secret.

episodes.name: Singing and Dancing
episodes.overview: Timmy wants to join a sinning group but may have a hard time keeping the secret from Russell. Jeff and Audrey have a new rude neighbor.

episodes.name: Jeff's Day
episodes.overview: Jeff's day goes as planned and is messed up when the house keeper drops by. Adam's eye twitches and he finds out what may cause it.

episodes.name: Zygote
episodes.overview: Jeff, Audrey and Brenda find a zygote after seeing a fertility specialist. Russell and Timmy double date.

episodes.name: Anniversary Chicken
episodes.overview: After Jeff stuns Audrey by remembering their wedding date the surprise is on Jeff. Timmy helps Russell on a date.

episodes.name: The Set Up
episodes.overview: Russell finds Timmy has a sister and wants to date her. Audrey and Jeff play match maker for their neighbor Liz.

episodes.name: Beating The System
episodes.overview: Jeff and Audrey are in for a big change when Brenda finds out she is pregnant. Timmy is Adam and Jennifer's wedding planner.

episodes.name: The Jeff Photo
episodes.overview: When an old photo of Jeff appears in an art gallery, he decides it's time to make some changes in his life. Meanwhile, Russell experiences a slump with women until he sees a familiar face.

episodes.name: Double Down
episodes.overview: Jeff and Audrey get a surprise that their family may soon double in size. Russell in his latest scheme to date a girl decides to throw a party Ford Timmy who recently became a citizen, now the question is will the party have the desired effect for Russell?

episodes.name: The Power Couple
episodes.overview: Russell gets Timmy and to see if he can figure out why to Liz is attracted to the other man and not Russell. Jeff doesn't like the idea that Audrey is making almost the same amount of money as he does.

episodes.name: The Last of the Red Hat Lovers
episodes.overview: Russell books a cruise that he thinks is filled with "red hot" ladies but instead it's filled with ladies from the Red Hat society. Meanwhile, Timmy tries to help Jeff and Audrey settle an argument.

episodes.overview: Audreyâ€™s throat surgery makes her unable to speak, much to Jeffâ€™s delight. Meanwhile, Russell tells Timmy the only way that he will get a raise is if he does Russellâ€™s dirty work and fires someone.

episodes.overview: Jen volunteers to throw Audrey a baby shower, but puts the wrong date on the invitation. Meanwhile, Jeff takes a liking to Audrey's maternity clothes, and Russell accomplishes great things when he decides to give up women.
